ial. We suggest that\nmost local tadpoles are bulge-free galaxy disks with lopsided star formation,\nperhaps from environmental effects such as ram pressure or disk impacts, or\nfrom a Jeans length comparable to half the disk size.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 12 Mar 2012 13:33:23 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-04"}
